Five wines and spirits joints in Jerusalem shopping centre were on Tuesday closed down for selling illicit and expired spirits. The outlets were also operating without liquor licences. The Nairobi county carried out the operations after three middle-aged men died after taking the illegal drinks last week. Read; Two dead after allegedly taking illicit brew in Kericho The operation was led by liquor board chairman Kennedy Odhiambo, area chief Nicholas Maingi and Embakasi West liquor Committee chairman Paul Ochieng. Odhiambo pledged to extend the operation to other estates. "We are going to close down all bars, wine and spirits operating near schools and in residential areas," Odhiambo said. Also read: Illicit liquor back, killing our legal alcohol business – Meru traders Click here for the latest political news 